the best father’s day gift… someone couldn’t wait any longer🤍
Levi Brooks Walker 
June 17, 2023 
8lbs, 22 inches 
we are so in love with you!

one week ago I did the hardest but most rewarding thing ever. nothing can prepare you for this or the love you’ll feel when you meet your little person. Brandon was my biggest support through it all, my mom was there through the entire night with me with no sleep, and after almost an hour and a half of pushing, we met our sweet little Levi. I wouldn’t trade any of this for the world. being a woman is the most empowering thing ever and I have a newfound appreciation for my body after getting my little baby here 🙏🏼 I can’t believe we have a one week old 😭🫶🏼 June 17th will forever be the day my life changed. #birth #pregnancy
I love being your mom 🤍

2 months 🤍👼🏼

Levi turned 2 months old yesterday & I’m fighting back tears. this past month:
- he recognizes mama & papa
- he smiles (not gas/milk drunk smiles)
- he is about to outgrow 0-3 month footies because he’s so tall
- he loves hey bear and ms rachel
- he sleeps 4 hours at a time through the night
- he eats 4/5 oz every hour and a half from his cow (me)
- he cuddles & sleeps with mama everyday 🫶🏼
- he went on a trip, boat & the US for the first time

we love you so much little ham! you are our entire world 🤍

1/2 a year with our boy!! 🥹🥲❤️🎄💌🎅🏻🫶🏼 the best 6 months of our lives! Levi is sleeping almost 12 hour stretches with no wake ups, is still breastfeeding & has solids 2x a day. He’s almost fully outgrown his 6-9 month clothes so starting to wear his 9-12 month outfits (mama could cry 😭). He loves Elmo & being lifted like an airplane, is almost fully sitting on his own & can fully roll from belly to back to belly again. He’s also babbling nonstop & has two teeth about to poke through 🥲. We love you little Levi!
